Appendix B. Reference simulation A at 700 K\par
\par
To test the validity of the CMG method at higher temperatures, reference simulation A (see\par
section 3) was rerun at a temperature of 700 K. First, using the procedure described in\par
appendix A and comparing the atomic positions at two different time frames of the simulation,\par
it was found that rmin = 0.9 \u197? and, therefore, cos \u952?max = 0.85. The other two parameters of\par
the algorithm (see table 1) were not changed. Next, the CMG algorithm was run. Figure 12\par
shows the atoms identified as belonging to moving dislocations, when comparing the atomic\par
